---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Enterprise PAM Engineering"
  description="Enterprise Privileged Access Management (PAM) case study: credential lifecycle automation, session governance, and integration architecture across AD/Entra ID and cloud IAM."
  ogType="article"
>
  <article class="space-y-8">
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p class="eyebrow">Case Study</p>
      <h1 class="section-title">Enterprise PAM Engineering</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Senior Solutions Architect and PAM subject matter expert at Netwrix, designing and deploying enterprise privileged access and identity management solutions for complex environments.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="card space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Scope</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-textMuted">
        <li>Credential lifecycle automation using Python, PowerShell, and API-driven orchestration.</li>
        <li>Session governance through proxied recording, monitoring, and just-in-time access controls.</li>
        <li>Service account policy enforcement with vaulting, rotation, and risk-based access pathways.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="card space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Integration Architecture</h2>
      <p class="text-textMuted">
        Designed PAM integration patterns tying together SIEM/SOAR telemetry, ITSM workflows, and CI/CD deployment
        controls. The objective was not just control enforcement, but resilient, auditable operations with minimal
        friction for delivery teams.
      </p>
      <p class="text-textMuted">
        Implementations emphasized deterministic onboarding, clean rollback paths, and measurable policy compliance.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="card space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Result</h2>
      <p class="text-textMuted">
        Delivered enterprise-grade privileged access platforms with repeatable automation patterns and governance models
        that held up under audit and production pressure.
      </p>
      <p class="text-textMuted">
        Recognized with the Netwrix Hero Award (Q1 FY&apos;25) for impact in enterprise PAM solution delivery.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</MainLayout>
